<HEAD>Polka Entrepreneur Appeals To Pierogi Lovers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fitness entrepreneur <PERSON> Andy </PERSON> <PERSON> LoRusso </PERSON> says he wrote `` The Pierogi Diet: 101 Fun Ways to Use and Enjoy Pierogis'' to help flatten the tummies of dance lovers as well as make them laugh. `` A lot of times when I dance at polka festivals, I see people dancing polka and drinking beer, and the one food they buy is dozens of pierogis,'' <PERSON> LoRusso </PERSON>, who sells `` PolkAerobics'' videotapes, said Friday. `` I want to reach these people.'' The book, which sells for $ 2.95, details ways to cut calories and enjoy pierogis, which are flour shells usually stuffed with potatoes, cheese or onions. It suggests topping pierogis with low-fat yogurt instead of sour cream and boiling the pasta pockets rather than frying them. It also suggests using the treats for less orthodox purposes. `` They can take the pierogi and stuff it in their clothes for shoulder pads or make a change purse out of one,'' <PERSON> LaRusso </PERSON> said. When promoting his book, <PERSON> LoRusso </PERSON> plays a kazoo and sings his latest song, `` The <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pierogi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Polka </LOCATION>.''
