<FIRST>r w PM-VAMortgageRates     06-03 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-VA Mortgage Rates,190</SECOND>
<HEAD>VA Cuts Rate to 10 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Veterans Affairs Department is reducing its home mortgage interest rates by half a percentage point, a move that could save purchasers more than $ 300 a year on a typical <ORGANIZATION> VA </ORGANIZATION> loan of $ 75,000. Effective Monday, the maximum interest rate for the federally backed loans will drop to 10 percent. It is the first change in the VA rate since Dec. 19, when the rate rose from 10 percent to 10.5 percent. VA home loans may be used to purchase, improve or refinance a home or condominium and to purchase or refinance a manufactured home. Secretary <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Derwinski </PERSON> said the action `` reflects continued investor confidence in the economy as well as current financial market conditions in which investors are willing to accept lower yields on long-term investments.'' The department said that effective Monday, a variety of other mortgage rates also will fall by a half-point. The maximum rate for graduated-payment mortgages will fall to 10.25 percent; home improvement loans, 11.5 percent; manufactured home loans, 12.5 percent; manufactured home lot-only loans, 12 percent; and manufactured home and lot loans, 12 percent.
