<HEAD>Iowa Crewman's Friend Recalls Talk of Suicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A sailor who survived the USS Iowa explosion says he heard his friend and crewmate talk of suicide but never of blowing up a ship. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> reported earlier Friday that investigators of the <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION> explosion are focusing on <PERSON> Clayton </PERSON> <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON>, who was one of the 47 sailors to die in the blast April 19. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON> was often despondent and aloof, and that he reportedly told a witness, `` If you've got to go, go in a blast. You go quick. You go painless.'' But <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON>'s friend, Gunner's Mate 3rd Class <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> <PERSON> Truitt </PERSON>, said on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Nightline'' that he did n't take <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON>'s talk of suicide seriously. `` The way he described, you know, killing himself would have been just simply -LRB- to -RRB- walk off the ship,'' <PERSON> Truitt </PERSON> said. `` He never talked about an explosion.'' <PERSON> Truitt </PERSON> said he remembered that <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON> `` was a little down, but it was over a year and a half ago. He had at one point -LRB- talked about suicide -RRB- but it was n't very serious. ... I think we all talk about suicide at least once in our life, and at the time the divisions were razzing him about how close friends we were.'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON>, 25, was the last man to touch the gunpowder that exploded in the ship's second turret on April 19. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> reported a witness told investigators that <PERSON> Hartwig </PERSON> showed off a $ 15 timer available in hobby stores and said that if it were rigged to a battery it could set off the ship's gunpowder and start a chain of explosions. But <PERSON> Truitt </PERSON>'s attorney, <PERSON> Ellis </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubin </PERSON>, said on `` Nightline'' tha