<HEAD>Fifteen Killed, 25 Injured as Bus Flips Over</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUKKUR, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A speeding bus full of wedding celebrants overturned on a curve near this southern Pakistani city, killing 15 people and injuring 25, officials said today. Police, speaking on the usual condition of anonymity, said the accident occurred early Friday when the driver apparently attempted to make the turn while traveling too fast. The driver fled the scene and was being sought for questioning, officers added. Thirteen people were instantly killed and two others died later, hospital officials said. All the victims, who reportedly belonged to the <LOCATION> Panhwar </LOCATION> tribe of <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>'s southern <LOCATION> Sindh </LOCATION> province, were celebrating a wedding.
