t would not cause renewed violence and conflicts,'' <PERSON> Botha </PERSON> was quoted as saying. He also rejected talks with the <ORGANIZATION> African </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> guerrilla movement or any other groups that use violence. <PERSON> Mandela </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> African </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> leader, many times has refused <LOCATION> Pretoria </LOCATION>'s offers of freedom because they are tied to a renunciation of violence. Welt am Sonntag released the text of the interview in advance of its publication Sunday.
