ntial Democratic candidates for governor were trying to drum up support. `` I think the bashing's over,'' said state Rep. <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Tucker </PERSON>, D-Andover. `` He's on his way out and people recognize that. The emphasis is on who's going to replace him.''
